🛠 Prerequisites
- Docker installed and running
- kubectl installed and configured

👉Recommended resource allocation for running a Vind cluster (1 master + 2 workers) on Docker Desktop (Windows):
- Master Node (Control Plane) → 2 vCPUs, 4 GB RAM
- Each Worker Node → 2 vCPUs, 3–4 GB RAM
- Cluster Total (1 master + 2 workers) → 6 vCPUs, 8–10 GB RAM


👉Install kubectl (if not already):

curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/windows/amd64/kubectl.exe"
mv kubectl.exe /c/Users/myuser/bin/
export PATH=$PATH:/c/Users/myuser/bin

👉Install vCluster CLI:
curl -s https://get.vcluster.com | bash

👉Create Vind cluster:
vcluster create vind-cluster --driver=docker --nodes=3

 You’ll get 3 nodes in total:
- 1 control plane (master)
- 2 worker nodes

👉Connect to cluster:
vcluster connect vind-cluster

👉Verify nodes:
kubectl get nodes

